element.name: Erie by Boreal Walker, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)
element.long-description:
I am of Irish heritage and would love to visit the country some day. If everything stays on track I should be there sometime in the next few years. Then I can visit this site myself. Other things on the short list is to visit the St. James' Gate Brewery and walk the yellow footsteps of Bloom through Dublin.
Thank you to Windsockers for helping me with this international exchange program.

2010-05-02T19:00:00Z : Found it by rooske
Quite prickly. TFTC

2010-03-28T19:00:00Z : Found it by Donnacha
Found on a quick trip out today.

2010-03-12T20:00:00Z : Found it by Fjon
Found it on my second visit. Quite a tricky hide.

2010-01-31T20:00:00Z : Found it by CluelessTwo
Thought we were 3rd to find this, as Hezekiah had FTF written at the top of the log. But I now see its been well visited. Nice view from here anyway.

2010-01-23T20:00:00Z : Didn't find it by Fjon
Not the most pleasant search. Very thorny here, and scratched myself nicely. Next a farmer came up and asked what I was doing near the gate. Once I got rid of him two dogs came running at me growling, so I jumped in the car and decided to call it a day.
